1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Every conference has sponsors.

2
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:11,425
And every sponsor expects to see their logo on the screens.

3
00:00:11,725 --> 00:00:15,475
In CueDeck, the Sponsor signage mode handles this automatically —

4
00:00:15,775 --> 00:00:19,525
you upload the logos, set how long each one displays,

5
00:00:19,825 --> 00:00:23,575
and they rotate in a clean fade loop on any

6
00:00:23,875 --> 00:00:25,875
display you assign them to.

7
00:00:26,175 --> 00:00:29,925
In this episode I'll show you how to upload sponsors,

8
00:00:30,225 --> 00:00:33,225
configure timing, and build a display sequence that

9
00:00:33,525 --> 00:00:36,900
rotates between sponsor branding and your session content automatically.

10
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,200
Sponsor logos are managed from the Signage panel.

11
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:43,125
There's a dedicated Sponsors section here —

12
00:00:43,425 --> 00:00:45,675
separate from your display configuration —

13
00:00:45,975 --> 00:00:48,600
where you manage the sponsor list that

14
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,900
feeds the Sponsor mode.

15
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:54,200
Each sponsor has a name, a logo file,

16
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,750
and a display duration in seconds.

17
00:00:57,050 --> 00:00:59,300
The list feeds every display that

18
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,850
is set to Sponsor mode —

19
00:01:02,150 --> 00:01:04,400
so you manage the logos once,

20
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:07,700
and they appear on all the relevant screens.

21
00:01:07,1000 --> 00:01:10,625
You can also set a sort order,

22
00:01:10,925 --> 00:01:12,925
which controls the rotation sequence.

23
00:01:13,225 --> 00:01:15,225
Let's add a sponsor.

24
00:01:15,525 --> 00:01:17,525
Click Add Sponsor.

25
00:01:17,825 --> 00:01:20,825
You'll get a small form: the sponsor's name,

26
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:24,125
a logo upload, and display duration in seconds.

27
00:01:24,425 --> 00:01:29,300
For the logo file: the recommended format is PNG with a transparent background.

28
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:33,350
This is important — the Sponsor mode renders on a

29
00:01:33,650 --> 00:01:38,150
dark background, so a PNG with transparency will look clean and professional.

30
00:01:38,450 --> 00:01:42,200
A white-background JPEG will look like a white rectangle in

31
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,750
the middle of a dark screen.

32
00:01:45,050 --> 00:01:48,425
Recommended size is 800 by 600 pixels or larger.

33
00:01:48,725 --> 00:01:51,725
CueDeck scales the image to fit the display,

34
00:01:52,025 --> 00:01:55,400
so going bigger is fine — it won't pixelate.

35
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:59,075
Going smaller may look soft on a large TV.

36
00:01:59,375 --> 00:02:03,125
I'll upload this sponsor logo, set the name to Platinum

37
00:02:03,425 --> 00:02:06,800
Partner, and set the display duration to eight seconds.

38
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:10,850
Hit Save — the logo uploads to the leod-assets storage

39
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:14,900
bucket and the sponsor is added to the rotation immediately.

40
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:17,825
Add as many sponsors as you need.

41
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:21,125
Each one gets its own duration setting —

42
00:02:21,425 --> 00:02:24,050
so if your title sponsor paid more,

43
00:02:24,350 --> 00:02:28,475
you can give them twelve seconds while other sponsors get six.

44
00:02:28,775 --> 00:02:31,775
The rotation respects the individual durations per sponsor,

45
00:02:32,075 --> 00:02:34,075
not a global setting.

46
00:02:34,375 --> 00:02:37,000
The sort order determines the rotation sequence.

47
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:41,050
Drag to reorder, or manually set the order number —

48
00:02:41,350 --> 00:02:43,975
your title sponsor can always appear first.

49
00:02:44,275 --> 00:02:48,025
Once the logos are uploaded, they're live immediately on any

50
00:02:48,325 --> 00:02:50,325
display running Sponsor mode.

51
00:02:50,625 --> 00:02:52,875
No page refresh, no redeploy —

52
00:02:53,175 --> 00:02:57,300
the display picks up the new sponsor via the realtime subscription.

53
00:02:57,600 --> 00:03:00,225
To show sponsors on a specific screen,

54
00:03:00,525 --> 00:03:03,525
open the display in the Signage panel and

55
00:03:03,825 --> 00:03:06,075
set the Content Mode to Sponsors.

56
00:03:06,375 --> 00:03:09,750
That display will now rotate through your sponsor list,

57
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:12,675
each logo displayed for its configured duration.

58
00:03:12,975 --> 00:03:14,975
Here's what it looks like.

59
00:03:15,275 --> 00:03:18,275
Clean, centred, full-screen logo on a dark background.

60
00:03:18,575 --> 00:03:21,575
After the configured duration, it fades out and

61
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:23,875
the next sponsor fades in.

62
00:03:24,175 --> 00:03:27,925
The transitions are smooth — no flash, no hard cut.

63
00:03:28,225 --> 00:03:31,225
If a sponsor has no logo uploaded —

64
00:03:31,525 --> 00:03:36,400
just a name — the mode renders the name in large text instead.

65
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:39,700
So you're never showing a broken image placeholder.

66
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,750
The most practical setup for venue displays isn't a screen

67
00:03:44,050 --> 00:03:46,050
that shows sponsors full-time.

68
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:51,225
It's a screen that cycles between useful session content and sponsor branding automatically.

69
00:03:51,525 --> 00:03:54,525
CueDeck has a sequence builder for exactly this.

70
00:03:54,825 --> 00:03:58,575
In the display edit modal, scroll down to the Sequence

71
00:03:58,875 --> 00:04:00,875
section and enable it.

72
00:04:01,175 --> 00:04:04,925
Then build your rotation: add a slide for the NextUp

73
00:04:05,225 --> 00:04:08,975
mode — the card showing what's on stage now and

74
00:04:09,275 --> 00:04:13,775
what's coming next — and set it to run for thirty seconds.

75
00:04:14,075 --> 00:04:17,075
Add a second slide for Sponsors mode and

76
00:04:17,375 --> 00:04:19,375
set it to ten seconds.

77
00:04:19,675 --> 00:04:21,675
Save the display.

78
00:04:21,975 --> 00:04:24,600
Now it runs: thirty seconds of NextUp,

79
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,525
ten seconds of sponsors, back to NextUp,

80
00:04:27,825 --> 00:04:30,075
back to sponsors — automatically, indefinitely.

81
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:34,125
You can build sequences with as many slides as you

82
00:04:34,425 --> 00:04:37,425
need, combining any of CueDeck's ten display modes:

83
00:04:37,725 --> 00:04:40,725
NextUp, Timeline, Programme, Sponsors, Clock, Countdown, and more.

84
00:04:41,025 --> 00:04:43,275
Each slide has its own duration.

85
00:04:43,575 --> 00:04:46,575
A few practical tips for sponsor logos that

86
00:04:46,875 --> 00:04:48,875
look professional on venue screens.

87
00:04:49,175 --> 00:04:51,175
Always use PNG with transparency.

88
00:04:51,475 --> 00:04:53,475
Never JPEG.

89
00:04:53,775 --> 00:04:55,775
Minimum 800 by 600 pixels.

90
00:04:56,075 --> 00:04:59,075
For a 4K screen, go 1600 by 900.

91
00:04:59,375 --> 00:05:02,375
If a sponsor only gives you a JPEG,

92
00:05:02,675 --> 00:05:04,925
open it in any image editor,

93
00:05:05,225 --> 00:05:08,225
remove the white background, and export as PNG.

94
00:05:08,525 --> 00:05:12,275
Ten minutes of prep prevents an embarrassing white box on

95
00:05:12,575 --> 00:05:14,825
a display during the coffee break.

96
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:18,500
Duration: eight to ten seconds is the sweet spot.

97
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:22,175
Long enough to read, short enough to keep rotating.

98
00:05:22,475 --> 00:05:25,100
Avoid anything shorter than five seconds —

99
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,650
logos need a moment to register.

100
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:30,950
And if you're running the Sequence mode —

101
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,500
mixing sponsors with session content —

102
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:38,675
the sponsor duration within the sequence is separate from the per-logo rotation duration.

103
00:05:38,975 --> 00:05:43,475
The sequence controls how long the display spends in Sponsor mode total.

104
00:05:43,775 --> 00:05:47,525
The per-logo duration controls how quickly it cycles through individual

105
00:05:47,825 --> 00:05:49,825
sponsors within that window.

106
00:05:50,125 --> 00:05:53,500
Upload your logos, set durations, build a sequence that

107
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,050
mixes sponsor time with session content,

108
00:05:56,350 --> 00:06:00,850
and every screen in the venue is handling your sponsor commitments automatically.

109
00:06:01,150 --> 00:06:03,775
That wraps up the signage series —

110
00:06:04,075 --> 00:06:06,075
Timeline, Programme, and Sponsors.

111
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:10,125
In the next episode we're going deeper into the display

112
00:06:10,425 --> 00:06:13,800
system: the full sequence builder, all ten display modes,

113
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:17,100
and how to configure a multi-zone venue where

114
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:20,400
different screens show different content for different audiences.

115
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,950
Subscribe so you don't miss it.
